WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:29.980
I didn't start getting [unintelligible] but I got a notice that they were going to rezone this property next to me. And um, I went down to the city to see about whether or not what - what I wanted to see this guy's building permit for what he's doing over there. And they had a building permit issued to him for five thousand dollars [unintelligible] to build [t]his water storage tank, which was allowed [unintelligible] zoning, supposedly. Well...

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:59.980
Uh.. it - it - it had a cover letter on it that said that it had nothing to do with the PDO that this [unintelligible] guy was proposing to rezone this property, which to me was a big red flag, I mean, you say it's not going [unintelligible] not nothing to do with something that it - or anything you know that it has something to do with anything and - uh - anyway I just

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:01.880
I could not believe this was going on.

00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:11.660
So, uh, we were going to have the second or third meeting, I can't remember anymore.

00:01:12.420 --> 00:01:22.640
But I went down, this guy here in town, his name was, uh, Mike.

00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:26.000
He was a graduate.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:30.460
He was, had a master's degree in city planning.

00:01:31.700 --> 00:01:35.040
And they happened to overhear me one day, and they said, well, come on, talk to him.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:41.580
He said that, uh, what they were doing was illegal, and that I should go get an attorney,

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:47.280
and that he'd recommended this guy named, uh, Deet, Dietze, out of, uh, Boulder.

00:01:47.860 --> 00:01:53.720
So I called this Dietze guy up for an appointment to go down and see him about whether or not I had a case against these people

00:01:53.720 --> 00:01:55.140
to stop the South Agate plan.

00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:55.860
So

00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:55.980
I

00:01:55.980 --> 00:02:00.920
went down there, and, uh, met with this Dietze.

00:02:02.120 --> 00:02:03.740
Can't even remember his name right now.

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:06.900
He was, this guy is, uh, cowardly thief.

00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:09.800
Man, he is a, he is a man of the system.

00:02:10.360 --> 00:02:15.100
And he, I mean, he milks me like I've never been milked before, I'll tell you.

00:02:15.540 --> 00:02:16.820
He, he is slick.

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:24.840
Um, but anyway, getting back to, see, at this meeting, I was going over these different things that were in the zoning ordinance

00:02:24.840 --> 00:02:28.180
that they weren't meeting, you know, the different requirements.

00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:31.140
And he kept telling me I didn't have a case, didn't have a case, didn't have a case.

00:02:31.220 --> 00:02:33.020
You know, every time I asked him a question.

00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:40.080
Finally, I told him, I said, uh, something to the effect that, uh, well, you know, they were building this, uh, concrete plant already,

00:02:40.080 --> 00:02:42.840
and, and I didn't know what to do.

00:02:42.920 --> 00:02:44.060
And he said, what do you mean you're building it?

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:52.820
He said, they can't build anything until, on this PDO property, until they've got final approval.

00:02:53.820 --> 00:02:54.700
He said, you've

00:02:54.700 --> 00:02:56.019
saved the best till last.

00:02:56.100 --> 00:03:00.019
He said, if that's true, if they've already issued the zoning permit, and I showed it to him.

00:03:00.500 --> 00:03:04.519
And I, I said, but they got this cover letter on it that says it has nothing to do with the PDO.

00:03:04.760 --> 00:03:06.720
He said, this is all bullshit by the town.

00:03:07.100 --> 00:03:10.459
He said, they, they cannot do anything on that property.

00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:11.880
So I said, okay.

00:03:12.239 --> 00:03:13.560
I said, this give me a lawsuit?

00:03:13.679 --> 00:03:14.519
Can we get him stopped?

00:03:14.620 --> 00:03:15.239
He said, yeah.

00:03:15.519 --> 00:03:20.920
He said, and he gave me the example of how some liquor store had, uh, built a liquor,

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:24.679
some town, people had built this building and put a liquor store in it.

00:03:24.859 --> 00:03:26.880
And, uh, it was never approved.

00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:29.519
And, uh, they ended up losing.

00:03:29.820 --> 00:03:32.560
And that, uh, that was what would happen here.

00:03:33.200 --> 00:03:35.500
Uh, the building wasn't taken down.

00:03:35.579 --> 00:03:37.480
They just put some other kind of business in it.

00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:41.560
But the liquor store had to go away because it wasn't zoned for that kind of a business.

00:03:41.799 --> 00:03:43.760
So he said, that's exactly what they're doing here.

00:03:44.019 --> 00:03:45.760
He said, we can stop this, no problem.

00:03:46.839 --> 00:03:52.720
So he told me to go up and take a bunch of pictures of what was going on about what they built.

00:03:52.799 --> 00:03:53.780
And I did this.

00:03:54.019 --> 00:03:54.679
And, uh, this.

00:03:54.700 --> 00:04:00.200
This, uh, Mike Carmody was his name.

00:04:01.019 --> 00:04:06.940
The guy here in Grand Lake that introduced, or referenced this Dietze guy to me.

00:04:07.440 --> 00:04:08.060
Mike Carmody.

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:11.620
I show him, I take all these pictures of his property.

00:04:12.079 --> 00:04:13.220
And I show them to Mike.

00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:15.320
And Mike comes down there and looks at it.

00:04:15.739 --> 00:04:21.000
And he, uh, he goes up to the concrete plant with me and sees all the dust that they're making and everything.

00:04:21.099 --> 00:04:21.940
And sees my plight.

00:04:22.340 --> 00:04:22.940
And agrees.

00:04:22.940 --> 00:04:23.860
You know, this is wrong.

00:04:24.700 --> 00:04:29.280
So I'm paying this Mike Carmody guy money for consulting or whatever.

00:04:29.940 --> 00:04:38.420
And, uh, I, uh, I told him that, uh, this Dietze guy was coming up at the next meeting to look.

00:04:38.700 --> 00:04:40.000
And he was going to be up here early.

00:04:40.099 --> 00:04:42.060
And I said, come dinner with us before the meeting.

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:43.980
And, uh, we'll go look at this.

00:04:44.039 --> 00:04:51.120
So Dietze came up and we drove around and we looked at this property, uh, out there that they were building on just west of me.

00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:54.599
And then I went, we went down to the restaurant.

00:04:54.700 --> 00:04:59.080
And Mike Carmody, I can't remember if he was with me or if he met me there afterwards.

00:04:59.080 --> 00:05:00.420
And I introduced him to Dietze.

00:05:00.420 --> 00:05:01.380
He must have met me there.

00:05:01.940 --> 00:05:09.700
So, uh, you know, we had this conversation about how Dietze could stop this because they were building there and they didn't have final approval there.

00:05:09.700 --> 00:05:10.820
You know, they bantered.

00:05:10.820 --> 00:05:13.780
We talked back and forth about what was [going/gonna] [unintelligible] the meeting was there.

00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:16.940
And Dietze went into the meeting with me.

00:05:17.820 --> 00:05:19.380
Listened to what they had to say.

00:05:19.820 --> 00:05:22.940
And, uh, and, you know, I don't know what was all said.

00:05:22.940 --> 00:05:24.700
But anyway, after the meeting, Dietze told me.

00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:26.700
He says, well, he says, they're not doing this right.

00:05:26.700 --> 00:05:32.940
He says, send me copies of all the meetings, minutes that have gone on and we'll, we'll look into this a little further.

00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:34.140
So I did that.

00:05:34.140 --> 00:05:39.099
I got copies of the previous meetings and, uh, sent them down to, uh, Dietze.

00:05:40.099 --> 00:05:43.700
Uh, I cannot remember his first name.

00:05:43.700 --> 00:05:44.700
I'll think of it later.

00:05:45.500 --> 00:05:48.460
Uh, so I sent these minutes down to Dietze.

00:05:48.940 --> 00:05:53.940
And, and, and, uh, they had left the zoning ordinance with Dietze

00:05:53.940 --> 00:05:54.500
the first

00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:55.500
time I was down there.

00:05:55.500 --> 00:05:59.500
And Dietze had been studying that ordinance to see what else it said.

00:05:59.500 --> 00:06:01.500
And he gets the copy of these minutes.

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:10.100
He calls me one day, about a week or so before this, uh, this, the town is supposed to have this final meeting for approval of this concrete plan.

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:14.100
He says, Marv, he says, uh, he says, there's something wrong here.

00:06:14.100 --> 00:06:15.700
He says, well, I've looked through these minutes.

00:06:15.700 --> 00:06:17.900
He says, are these the only meetings that they've had?

00:06:17.900 --> 00:06:19.500
And that was the truth.

00:06:19.500 --> 00:06:21.100
I says, that's all the meetings they've had.

00:06:21.100 --> 00:06:23.700
He says, well, if, if this is all the meetings they've had.

00:06:23.700 --> 00:06:27.700
They have a serious procedural error here.

00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:30.700
At least that's what he called it later on.

00:06:30.700 --> 00:06:34.700
Uh, he says, they've left out at least two public hearings.

00:06:34.700 --> 00:06:41.700
And, uh, basically they're trying to short circuit this whole process to get this approved.

00:06:41.700 --> 00:06:43.700
And I says, well, great.

00:06:43.700 --> 00:06:46.700
I says, that just adds to our case, right?

00:06:46.700 --> 00:06:47.700
And he says, no.

00:06:47.700 --> 00:06:48.700
He says, this is the case.

00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:52.700
He says, he says, we don't even have to worry about the, the up zoning.

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:54.700
Uh, as far as them building there.

00:06:54.700 --> 00:06:57.700
He says, we can stop it based on this.

00:06:57.700 --> 00:06:59.700
So I says, well, great.

00:06:59.700 --> 00:07:00.700
I says, how do we go about this?

00:07:00.700 --> 00:07:03.700
He says, well, he says, we go and we tell them.

00:07:03.700 --> 00:07:08.700
And, uh, I says, well, I says, if it'll get it stopped, if it's, it'll be a done deal.

00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:10.700
I says, let's get it done.

00:07:10.700 --> 00:07:11.700
Let's stop it.

00:07:11.700 --> 00:07:21.700
So he wrote up this letter to the town, how they were doing it wrong, and brought it up with him at the meeting, uh, the final meeting.

00:07:21.700 --> 00:07:24.700
And explained to him how they were doing this wrong.

00:07:24.700 --> 00:07:31.700
And of course, Docheff's attorney is all defensive, and the town attorney is all defensive, but they're doing it right.

00:07:31.700 --> 00:07:37.700
And Dietze continues to explain to him how they've left out these public hearings.

00:07:37.700 --> 00:07:41.700
And then the, they have to take a break.

00:07:41.700 --> 00:07:42.700
Okay.

00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:46.700
And of course, all along, I had contended with the town that this was pre-approved.

00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:49.700
And they said it wasn't, of course.

00:07:49.700 --> 00:07:51.700
And I says, well, why did you issue the

00:07:51.700 --> 00:07:52.700
building permit.

00:07:52.700 --> 00:07:56.700
And they said that they could because that was allowable in M-2-D zoning.

00:07:56.700 --> 00:07:59.700
But what, what, and this is interesting.

00:07:59.700 --> 00:08:04.700
Later on, this, an article came out in our local paper.

00:08:04.700 --> 00:08:06.700
There were a lot of articles about this.

00:08:06.700 --> 00:08:14.700
Um, of course, it was, uh, September 7th of 2000 in the Sky High News.

00:08:14.700 --> 00:08:19.700
There was an article about how Granby tickets Mountain View muffler over junk. And they've got

00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:21.700
a little caption on the picture.

00:08:21.700 --> 00:08:22.700
of my building, it

00:08:22.700 --> 00:08:23.700
says, ticketed.

00:08:23.700 --> 00:08:27.700
Mountain View muffler was ticketed by the town of Granby for a junk violation.

00:08:27.700 --> 00:08:33.700
In the foreground is the foundation for a proposed concrete back plant proposed for

00:08:33.700 --> 00:08:35.700
a site near Mountain View muffler.

00:08:35.700 --> 00:08:40.700
Well, it didn't occur to me at the time when this article came out that how can you have

00:08:40.700 --> 00:08:44.700
a foundation for a proposed concrete plant?

00:08:44.700 --> 00:08:49.700
Everybody knew that this concrete plant was going in, even though they hadn't had final

00:08:49.700 --> 00:08:50.700
approval yet.

00:08:50.700 --> 00:08:51.700
And this was a joke.

00:08:51.700 --> 00:08:54.700
I mean, the whole community knew that this was going to happen.

00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:56.700
And I knew it was going to happen.

00:08:56.700 --> 00:09:02.700
But I was basically listening to this Dietze that this was going to get stopped.

00:09:02.700 --> 00:09:07.700
Well, what he, he told them this and what they had a big recess in this meeting and

00:09:07.700 --> 00:09:08.700
went outside.

00:09:08.700 --> 00:09:10.700
They're all screaming at each other.

00:09:10.700 --> 00:09:15.700
And they're, they're, uh, they go back in after 15 minutes and sit down and lo and behold,

00:09:15.700 --> 00:09:17.700
it doesn't stop anything.

00:09:17.700 --> 00:09:18.700
The town

00:09:18.700 --> 00:09:19.700
makes this

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:20.700
resolution 2000

00:09:20.700 --> 00:09:21.700
that, uh,

00:09:21.700 --> 00:09:22.700
this

00:09:22.700 --> 00:09:23.700
is a, uh,

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:24.700
this is a,

00:09:24.700 --> 00:09:31.240
not a final meeting even though it's been advertised in a local paper as, in the public

00:09:31.240 --> 00:09:36.620
notices, the newspaper Patrick Brower, the editor has written an article that this is

00:09:36.620 --> 00:09:41.140
the final meeting and it should meet approval because it's such an important thing.

00:09:41.140 --> 00:09:42.140
It's needed by the community.

00:09:42.140 --> 00:09:46.700
Well, it was needed, but it should have stayed where it was up there in the concrete plant,

00:09:46.700 --> 00:09:48.260
uh, up in the gravel pit.

00:09:48.260 --> 00:09:51.240
uh... besides this guy, owned, this

00:09:51.240 --> 00:09:55.380
Docheff guy owned five acres right there by the gravel pit. He could have

00:09:55.380 --> 00:09:56.620
put it there

00:09:56.620 --> 00:09:58.319
he didn't need to uh...

00:09:58.319 --> 00:10:02.000
to rezone anything he could have put it right there

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:03.400
but he, you know, this guy

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:05.760
had this hard on for me that

00:10:05.760 --> 00:10:08.780
for ten years so that he was going to get even with me

00:10:08.780 --> 00:10:10.380
said this in so many words

00:10:10.380 --> 00:10:13.260
on more than one occasion

00:10:13.260 --> 00:10:14.420
and uh...

00:10:14.420 --> 00:10:16.280
anyway well he was doing it that

00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:17.700
whatever you know

00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:21.960
i'm fighting for my life because this is my future this is my retirement

00:10:21.960 --> 00:10:23.880
i need to get this uh...

00:10:23.880 --> 00:10:27.100
this uh...  stopped.

00:10:27.100 --> 00:10:28.000
well anyway

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:30.360
they made this resolution two thousand

00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:32.380
that they're at, they're uh...

00:10:32.380 --> 00:10:33.160
they...

00:10:33.160 --> 00:10:33.940
are at

00:10:33.940 --> 00:10:38.200
a preliminary meeting and they're making uh certain that everybody knows it

00:10:38.200 --> 00:10:39.040
now

00:10:39.040 --> 00:10:42.900
and uh... that they can do this. Well...

00:10:42.900 --> 00:10:45.000
Dietze tells me, of course,

00:10:45.000 --> 00:10:47.200
they're still, it's illegal, they can't do it.

00:10:47.200 --> 00:10:47.700
You know

00:10:47.700 --> 00:10:49.940
they had the final meeting advertised,

00:10:49.940 --> 00:10:52.080
they're at the final meeting and now they're

00:10:52.080 --> 00:10:52.920
changing it,

00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:55.300
and saying that it's a pri - preliminary meeting.

00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:59.840
and he convinces me that we still gotta a good case. He says they can go on and do whatever

00:10:59.840 --> 00:11:00.920
whatever they want

00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:03.700
we're gonna get this stopped. So I,

00:11:03.700 --> 00:11:04.860
of course, believe him,

00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:07.260
and i just keep paying him. And up until that time

00:11:07.260 --> 00:11:11.140
I paid him probably about five thousand dollars.

00:11:11.140 --> 00:11:15.180
Anyway we got this lawsuit going on and this newspaper guy

00:11:15.180 --> 00:11:15.700
Patrick Brower,

00:11:15.700 --> 00:11:24.300
this guy is this - this guy is the scum of the earth also, which is most - most, so many of these people up here are for different reasons.

00:11:24.700 --> 00:11:33.040
But this guy hated me because when I first came up here in 91, the gambling issue was getting started up here.

00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:39.260
And I'm just sitting around my condo reading this newspaper, and this guy is just blasting.

00:11:39.700 --> 00:11:44.240
I mean, he's just belittling them and slandering them as far as I was concerned.

00:11:44.240 --> 00:11:47.180
They're just making the pro gamblers look like fools.

00:11:47.300 --> 00:11:49.300
And I thought, well, what's wrong with these people?

00:11:49.340 --> 00:11:50.860
They've got no economy up here.

00:11:52.240 --> 00:11:58.000
Here's something that's happened down there in Black Hawk and over at Cripple Creek,

00:11:58.100 --> 00:12:01.440
and it's done good economic things for those communities.

00:12:01.820 --> 00:12:03.100
Why is he so against this?

00:12:03.120 --> 00:12:04.080
I never could understand it.

00:12:04.120 --> 00:12:10.280
So I finally, after he blasted some people that I knew here in town, I wrote him a letter and told him,

00:12:10.360 --> 00:12:12.980
hey, this is America, you know, leave these people alone.

00:12:13.640 --> 00:12:13.860
This is...

00:12:14.240 --> 00:12:19.320
You don't have to be making them look like some kind of fools, you know.

00:12:20.520 --> 00:12:22.140
That was the whole gist of my letter.

00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:25.920
Anyway, you know, he just didn't know who Marv Heemeyer was,

00:12:25.920 --> 00:12:32.860
but he definitely hated me because I, you know, said some things in the paper that were right on the button.

00:12:33.040 --> 00:12:35.480
I mean, I had an attorney for a neighbor at the time.

00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:41.640
His name was Sommermeyer, Mayo - uh - "Butch" Sommermeyer.

00:12:42.040 --> 00:12:43.620
Called him, his first name was Mayo.

00:12:43.760 --> 00:12:44.220
He's out of Fort

00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:45.180
Collins, I believe.

00:12:45.580 --> 00:12:47.980
But they had the house down below me here, and he said,

00:12:48.060 --> 00:12:51.100
Marv, he says, what you're saying in the newspaper is exactly right.

00:12:51.240 --> 00:12:52.660
You know, he says, I'm all behind you.

00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:55.720
And it was encouraging, you know.

00:12:55.800 --> 00:12:58.240
Well, you know, this is small-town politics,

00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:02.500
and what do I know about small-town politics other than they're usually not good?

00:13:03.180 --> 00:13:07.060
And I just figured, well, I'm kind of immune to a lot of this,

00:13:07.080 --> 00:13:08.560
and this was back in 92 yet,

00:13:09.720 --> 00:13:14.220
and didn't realize how much it was going to affect what I was doing,

00:13:14.240 --> 00:13:16.480
and this newspaper guy, Patrick Brower,

00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:21.400
had told me after I started the muffler shops on a couple of different occasions,

00:13:21.540 --> 00:13:26.000
because I called him, and I was advertising with him and so forth.

00:13:26.300 --> 00:13:29.680
He said that he was going to come down and we'd do an article on my little business.

00:13:30.060 --> 00:13:31.340
Well, he never did do it.

00:13:31.820 --> 00:13:38.320
You know, he was doing everything he could to keep me from getting any additional publicity.

00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:44.220
It's one of those, it's a kind of a community that in order for you to get

00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:47.420
ahead you have to keep the neighbor down.

00:13:47.560 --> 00:13:50.520
You've got to keep, you've got to be bad-mouthing everybody.

00:13:50.760 --> 00:13:54.340
It's not, you know, build yourself up on your own merits.

00:13:54.760 --> 00:13:58.640
It's tear the other guy down however you can do it, legally, of course.

00:13:59.760 --> 00:14:01.300
I'm going to take a break here.

00:14:01.620 --> 00:14:03.020
I guess I'm not going to take a break.

00:14:03.640 --> 00:14:05.040
I'll lose my train of thought.

00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:09.660
Anyway, this Patrick Brower, I mean, he's a pothead.

00:14:10.640 --> 00:14:12.360
Of course, you can't tell anybody that.

00:14:12.880 --> 00:14:14.080
You know.

00:14:14.240 --> 00:14:18.000
Big liberal, army brat, has had everything in his life given to him.

00:14:18.600 --> 00:14:22.280
You know, but he knows how to abuse the power of the pen.

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:25.440
And that's a big thing up here is abuse of power.

00:14:26.980 --> 00:14:30.580
They said that to me one time that I didn't have any respect for authority.

00:14:31.060 --> 00:14:33.100
And that's not the truth at all.

00:14:33.340 --> 00:14:36.200
The truth is I have the utmost respect for authority.

00:14:36.640 --> 00:14:37.740
But they don't.

00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:40.680
They didn't respect the FDIC or its procedures.

00:14:40.860 --> 00:14:44.180
They don't respect good people coming in

00:14:44.400 --> 00:14:45.840
the community.

00:14:45.840 --> 00:14:47.840
They only respect what they want.

00:14:47.840 --> 00:14:50.840
And if they're in that power circle, that's the way it's going to be.

00:14:50.840 --> 00:14:51.840
They believe.

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:55.440
And you're not going to get in if you've done anything to offend them in any way.

00:14:55.440 --> 00:15:00.440
Well, I guess that's their right in America.

00:15:00.440 --> 00:15:02.440
But I've got my rights too.

00:15:02.440 --> 00:15:06.440
Maybe they're wrong when I exercise these rights, but I really don't care.

00:15:06.440 --> 00:15:12.440
I am going to exercise this right because we are given this freedom to do what we want to do.

00:15:12.440 --> 00:15:14.020
Until we do something wrong.

00:15:14.020 --> 00:15:16.020
And then we have to pay for it.

00:15:16.020 --> 00:15:20.020
Well, these people have figured out a pretty good way, being a small community,

00:15:20.020 --> 00:15:23.020
how to get away with doing things wrong and doing it legally.

00:15:23.020 --> 00:15:27.020
And I'll get into that a little bit more later on.

00:15:27.020 --> 00:15:32.020
But getting back to the newspaper article,

00:15:32.020 --> 00:15:38.020
I mean, how can you have a friggin' foundation for a proposed concrete plan?

00:15:38.020 --> 00:15:41.020
You know, this was a pre-approved deal.

00:15:41.020 --> 00:15:43.020
And - And I

00:15:43.020 --> 00:15:44.020
just didn't - I've never been

00:15:44.020 --> 00:15:47.020
through any town politics before. But because

00:15:47.020 --> 00:15:51.020
this was affecting me so adversely I was definitely learning.

00:15:51.020 --> 00:15:54.020
And, you know, but it was always a day laying a dollar short with

00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:57.020
me, and my attorney wasn't helping me at all.

00:15:57.020 --> 00:15:59.020
It was kind of sad.  And the

00:15:59.020 --> 00:16:02.020
town paper was actually...  Ehh yeah...

00:16:02.020 --> 00:16:09.020
This Brower guy was pissed off as hell when he found out that we'd caught the town with their pants down.

00:16:09.020 --> 00:16:13.020
You know, he wrote in the paper that I'd gotten some hot shot attorney out of Boulder

00:16:13.020 --> 00:16:15.020
to stop this whole thing.

00:16:15.020 --> 00:16:17.020
And he was no hot shot attorney.

00:16:17.020 --> 00:16:19.020
He was doing his job.

00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:23.020
Which, getting back to that personally,

00:16:23.020 --> 00:16:29.020
I believe with all my heart that both the town attorney and Daley...

00:16:29.020 --> 00:16:32.020
Rich Daley was Docheff's attorney.

00:16:32.020 --> 00:16:35.020
And the town attorney...

00:16:35.020 --> 00:16:37.020
I forget his name right now.

00:16:37.020 --> 00:16:39.020
For Granby, the same one for Grand Lake.

00:16:39.020 --> 00:16:42.020
They were in cahoots on this deal.

00:16:42.020 --> 00:16:48.020
Where they figured that no one would know the procedure

00:16:48.020 --> 00:16:51.020
because they had never done a PDO before.

00:16:51.020 --> 00:16:52.020
A commercial PDO.

00:16:52.020 --> 00:16:55.020
And they figured that what did they have to lose?

00:16:55.020 --> 00:16:58.020
They would just go ahead and try to get this through.

00:16:58.020 --> 00:17:01.020
And it would probably go through, no problem.

00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:06.020
But of course this hot shot attorney, according to the paper, caught them with their pants down.

00:17:06.020 --> 00:17:09.020
Well, do you think that they would ever thank me

00:17:09.020 --> 00:17:12.020
for putting them on the straight and narrow?

00:17:12.020 --> 00:17:13.020
On the right path?

00:17:13.020 --> 00:17:15.020
To get this done right?

00:17:15.020 --> 00:17:16.020
No.

00:17:16.020 --> 00:17:17.020
You know?

00:17:17.020 --> 00:17:18.020
And I agree.

00:17:18.020 --> 00:17:19.020
I screwed up.

00:17:19.020 --> 00:17:20.020
That's what I'm agreeing to.

00:17:20.020 --> 00:17:21.020
Screw it up.

00:17:21.020 --> 00:17:24.020
We should have never told them what we did.

00:17:24.020 --> 00:17:26.020
And as a matter of fact, the night of that final meeting,

00:17:26.020 --> 00:17:29.020
when they made that resolution,

00:17:29.020 --> 00:17:33.020
or the night that he pointed out to them that they were doing this wrong,

00:17:33.020 --> 00:17:37.020
at 2.30 in the morning, I sent this Dietze attorney of mine,

00:17:37.020 --> 00:17:39.020
at 2.30 in the morning, an email.

00:17:39.020 --> 00:17:41.020
Because I came home

00:17:41.020 --> 00:17:44.020
after the meeting and read the ordinance again.

00:17:44.020 --> 00:17:48.020
And I said, I think that we've spoken too soon.

00:17:48.020 --> 00:17:51.020
And that we shouldn't have told them.

00:17:51.020 --> 00:17:54.020
That we should have let them have the final meeting.

00:17:54.020 --> 00:17:59.020
And that we actually should have had a lawsuit filed 30 days later.

00:17:59.020 --> 00:18:01.020
Had we done it that way,

00:18:01.020 --> 00:18:06.020
we would have been able to get an injunction against the building that was continuing.

00:18:06.020 --> 00:18:10.020
We probably could have gotten some of my attorney's fees,

00:18:10.020 --> 00:18:12.020
all of my attorney's fees,

00:18:12.020 --> 00:18:17.020
and actually made these people out,

00:18:17.020 --> 00:18:23.020
this town attorney and this Rich Daly and the Docheffs and the town council

00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:25.020
and the planning commission,

00:18:25.020 --> 00:18:36.020
to show the town the real mafia-type tactics that they were using.

00:18:36.020 --> 00:18:38.020
And that's all they are.

00:18:38.020 --> 00:18:40.020
They're criminals.

00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:42.020
You know, they bend the law,

00:18:42.020 --> 00:18:45.020
and they got caught, and that pissed them off.

00:18:45.020 --> 00:18:48.020
And, you know, so now they really hate me.

00:18:48.020 --> 00:18:50.020
Well, I'm sorry, you know.

00:18:50.020 --> 00:18:53.020
It's my future. It's my life.

00:18:53.020 --> 00:18:55.020
I am an independent business person,

00:18:55.020 --> 00:19:00.020
and only I am responsible for my future and my income and my livelihood.

00:19:00.020 --> 00:19:02.020
And they're threatening that.

00:19:02.020 --> 00:19:08.020
And they're pissed off because I'm trying to defend my property and my livelihood against this.

00:19:08.020 --> 00:19:10.020
And that doesn't make any sense.

00:19:10.020 --> 00:19:11.020
You know?

00:19:11.020 --> 00:19:15.020
Well, anyway, I'm just getting a little upset here,

00:19:15.020 --> 00:19:17.020
so let me try to settle down.

00:19:17.020 --> 00:19:19.020
Get back to the point here.

00:19:19.020 --> 00:19:23.020
We, uh, I'm not happy with the attorney,

00:19:23.020 --> 00:19:24.020
but what choice do I have?

00:19:24.020 --> 00:19:26.020
They've done this Resolution 2000.

00:19:26.020 --> 00:19:27.020
They go on with these meetings.

00:19:27.020 --> 00:19:29.020
He's telling me that they're still illegal.

00:19:29.020 --> 00:19:30.020
We're going to go to court.

00:19:30.020 --> 00:19:31.020
We're going to win.

00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:33.020
And, of course, it's all salesmanship.

00:19:33.020 --> 00:19:36.020
And I'm supposed to, and I'm talking to this Mike Carmody guy,

00:19:36.020 --> 00:19:37.020
who's supposed to be consulting with me.

00:19:37.020 --> 00:19:39.020
He says, Dietze is right.

00:19:39.020 --> 00:19:41.020
He says, they're doing this wrong.

00:19:41.020 --> 00:19:43.020
So I've got two people telling me that Dietze is wrong.

00:19:43.020 --> 00:19:45.020
I mean, I told Carmody I thought he screwed up,

00:19:45.020 --> 00:19:48.020
but Carmody says, no, no, Dietze knows what he's doing.

00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:53.020
Well, Dietze didn't know what he was doing.

00:19:53.020 --> 00:19:57.020
Or else the corruption up here is worse than I thought.

00:19:57.020 --> 00:19:59.020
And it is. It is.

00:19:59.020 --> 00:20:03.020
I have no concept of how corrupt these people can be.

00:20:03.020 --> 00:20:06.020
But anyway, you know, I'm looking.

00:20:06.020 --> 00:20:08.020
My business has gone to hell.

00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:13.020
Oh, and getting back to 99, when these first meetings were coming,

00:20:13.020 --> 00:20:16.020
when we were going through all this approval,

00:20:16.020 --> 00:20:23.020
it was in 99 that I went, I think we'd already started the lawsuit.

00:20:23.020 --> 00:20:26.020
And they're going to put in water and sewer to this 22 acres,

00:20:26.020 --> 00:20:28.020
or they're going to get it approved.

00:20:28.020 --> 00:20:33.020
And, you know, I'm wanting my water and sewer hooked up.

00:20:33.020 --> 00:20:36.020
And I made this known in the minutes.

00:20:36.020 --> 00:20:37.020
At the. . .

00:20:38.020 --> 00:20:41.020
Planning Commission meeting and the Town Council meeting.

00:20:41.020 --> 00:20:51.020
And the guy who owned a motel over there, Boyce was his name,

00:20:51.020 --> 00:20:55.020
from the Boyce Insurance Agents, David Boyce, I believe his name is,

00:20:55.020 --> 00:20:59.020
had made a written request that they have water and sewer easements

00:20:59.020 --> 00:21:02.020
to their motels, to that section of land.

00:21:02.020 --> 00:21:03.020
They weren't in the town.

00:21:03.020 --> 00:21:04.020
It was county-owned

00:21:04.020 --> 00:21:06.020
pro er - it was county zone property.

00:21:06.020 --> 00:21:08.020
But they wanted rights to get

00:21:08.020 --> 00:21:10.020
to the water and sewer.

00:21:10.020 --> 00:21:12.020
And, you know, I told this to Carmody, and Carmody says,

00:21:12.020 --> 00:21:15.020
well, yeah, he says, they have to give that to you, too.

00:21:15.020 --> 00:21:17.020
And that's why I asked for it.

00:21:17.020 --> 00:21:21.020
They could not discriminate against me as a neighbor.

00:21:21.020 --> 00:21:24.020
If I wanted water and sewer, they had to give that to me, too.

00:21:24.020 --> 00:21:26.020
So I believe that's what was happening.

00:21:26.020 --> 00:21:29.020
Although I never asked, sent them a formal letter requesting it.

00:21:29.020 --> 00:21:31.020
It was just mentioned at the meeting.

00:21:31.020 --> 00:21:32.020
All right.

00:21:32.020 --> 00:21:36.020
And I had gone down to the water and sanitation district in 99

00:21:36.020 --> 00:21:43.020
to review the minutes back from 92 to see what we had all discussed

00:21:43.020 --> 00:21:49.020
and why I wasn't allowed on the, and I hadn't been annexed in at that time.

00:21:49.020 --> 00:21:52.020
I go down to the water and sanitation district and get these minutes,

00:21:52.020 --> 00:21:56.020
and I start reading them, and I really can't believe these minutes

00:21:56.020 --> 00:22:01.020
because there is not one mention of a maintenance easement being required

00:22:01.020 --> 00:22:05.020
for them in order to allow me into these, you know,

00:22:05.020 --> 00:22:07.020
into the sanitation district.

00:22:07.020 --> 00:22:09.020
There's not one mention of it.

00:22:09.020 --> 00:22:15.020
And that was probably 15 minutes of the discussion at the water meeting that night

00:22:15.020 --> 00:22:20.020
back in the fall of 92 was that I didn't have this maintenance easement.

00:22:20.020 --> 00:22:25.020
And I was just amazed that they had changed the minutes

00:22:25.020 --> 00:22:28.020
to reflect that we hadn't talked about that.

00:22:28.020 --> 00:22:34.020
Well, I come to find out later the reason they eliminated that from being in the minutes

00:22:34.020 --> 00:22:36.020
was because if it ev...
